body_html:
@kayzhu @eliben

Decided to make a new squashed version instead of the merge that included a whole lot of other stuff.

It passes some of the XLA unit tests (you would need pull request #9759 to be able to run the unit tests).

It crashes on a couple, and it hangs on the variable test, not sure why, breaking into it shows the evaluator executing binary ops. but mostly it just complains errors out with unsupported ops.

nevertheless - this pull request could be useful to you.

body:
@kayzhu @eliben 

Decided to make a new squashed version instead of the merge that included a whole lot of other stuff.

It passes some of the XLA unit tests (you would need pull request https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/9759 to be able to run the unit tests).

It crashes on a couple, and it hangs on the variable test, not sure why, breaking into it shows the evaluator executing binary ops.  but mostly it just complains errors out with unsupported ops.

nevertheless - this pull request could be useful to you.
